dc:description: Buff clay with worn reddish brown and brown glaze. Short nozzle broken off, ended in straight groove at base with small stamped circle at either side. Plain rim. Two molded rings set off by grooves between rim and discus. Four-leaved rosettes on discus with filling -hole as center. Air hole at base of nozzle. Ring handle, two grooves on upper half. Slightly raised base set off by circular stamp.
